// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// BankPortal — backend-2fa — Jenkins Pipeline Declarativo
// SOFIA DevOps Agent — FEAT-001 v1.0.0
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
pipeline {
  agent { label 'sofia-agent' }

  environment {
    SERVICE_NAME    = 'backend-2fa'
    REGISTRY        = "${env.DOCKER_REGISTRY}"
    IMAGE_TAG       = "${env.GIT_COMMIT[0..7]}"
    K8S_NAMESPACE   = 'bankportal'
    SONAR_PROJECT   = 'bankportal-backend-2fa'
  }

  options {
    timeout(time: 30, unit: 'MINUTES')
    buildDiscarder(logRotator(numToKeepStr: '20'))
    disableConcurrentBuilds()
  }

  triggers {
    // Solo en feature/* y develop — el tag v* tiene su propio trigger
    pollSCM('H/5 * * * *')
  }

  stages {

    // ── MONOREPO PATH FILTER ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    stage('Path Filter') {
      steps {
        script {
          def changes = sh(
            script: "git diff --name-only HEAD~1 HEAD | grep '^apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/' | wc -l",
            returnStdout: true
          ).trim().toInteger()
          if (changes == 0 && !env.TAG_NAME) {
            currentBuild.result = 'NOT_BUILT'
            error("No changes in ${SERVICE_NAME} — pipeline skipped")
          }
          echo "Changes detected in ${SERVICE_NAME}: ${changes} files"
        }
      }
    }

    // ── CI ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    stage('Unit Tests') {
      steps {
        dir("apps/${SERVICE_NAME}") {
          sh 'mvn test -Dsurefire.failIfNoSpecifiedTests=false -q'
        }
      }
      post {
        always {
          junit "apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/target/surefire-reports/**/*.xml"
          jacoco(
            execPattern: "apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/target/jacoco.exec",
            classPattern:  "apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/target/classes",
            sourcePattern: "apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/src/main/java",
            minimumLineCoverage: '80'
          )
        }
      }
    }

    stage('SAST — SonarQube') {
      steps {
        dir("apps/${SERVICE_NAME}") {
          withSonarQubeEnv('sonarqube-sofia') {
            sh """
              mvn sonar:sonar \
                -Dsonar.projectKey=${SONAR_PROJECT} \
                -Dsonar.projectName='BankPortal :: backend-2fa' \
                -Dsonar.coverage.jacoco.xmlReportPaths=target/site/jacoco/jacoco.xml \
                -q
            """
          }
        }
      }
    }

    stage('Quality Gate') {
      steps {
        timeout(time: 5, unit: 'MINUTES') {
          waitForQualityGate abortPipeline: true
        }
      }
    }

    stage('Build Docker Image') {
      steps {
        dir("apps/${SERVICE_NAME}") {
          // Build del JAR antes de construir la imagen
          sh 'mvn package -DskipTests -q'
        }
        sh """
          docker build \
            --build-arg BUILD_DATE=\$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \
            --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=${env.GIT_COMMIT} \
            --build-arg VERSION=${env.TAG_NAME ?: IMAGE_TAG} \
            -t ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG} \
            -t ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:latest-dev \
            -f apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/Dockerfile \
            apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/
        """
      }
    }

    stage('Vulnerability Scan — Trivy') {
      steps {
        sh """
          trivy image \
            --exit-code 1 \
            --severity CRITICAL,HIGH \
            --no-progress \
            --format table \
            ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}
        """
      }
    }

    // ── CD DEV ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    stage('Push & Deploy — DEV') {
      when { branch 'develop' }
      steps {
        withCredentials([usernamePassword(
            credentialsId: 'docker-registry-creds',
            usernameVariable: 'REG_USER',
            passwordVariable: 'REG_PASS')]) {
          sh "docker login ${REGISTRY} -u ${REG_USER} -p ${REG_PASS}"
          sh "docker push ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG}"
          sh "docker push ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:latest-dev"
        }
        // Rolling update en namespace DEV
        sh """
          kubectl set image deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} \
            ${SERVICE_NAME}=${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG} \
            -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE}-dev
          kubectl rollout status deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} \
            -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE}-dev \
            --timeout=120s
        """
      }
    }

    stage('Smoke Tests — DEV') {
      when { branch 'develop' }
      steps {
        sh """
          # Health check básico post-deploy
          for i in 1 2 3 4 5; do
            STATUS=\$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' \
              http://backend-2fa.bankportal-dev.svc/actuator/health/readiness)
            if [ "\$STATUS" = "200" ]; then
              echo "Smoke test PASS — HTTP \$STATUS"
              exit 0
            fi
            echo "Attempt \$i — HTTP \$STATUS — retrying in 10s..."
            sleep 10
          done
          echo "Smoke test FAILED — service not healthy after 50s"
          exit 1
        """
      }
    }

    // ── CD STG / PROD (disparado por tag vX.Y.Z) ────────────────────────────
    stage('Push Release Image') {
      when { tag 'v*' }
      steps {
        withCredentials([usernamePassword(
            credentialsId: 'docker-registry-creds',
            usernameVariable: 'REG_USER',
            passwordVariable: 'REG_PASS')]) {
          sh "docker login ${REGISTRY} -u ${REG_USER} -p ${REG_PASS}"
          sh "docker tag ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG} ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${env.TAG_NAME}"
          sh "docker push ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${env.TAG_NAME}"
        }
      }
    }

    stage('Deploy — STG') {
      when { tag 'v*' }
      steps {
        sh """
          kubectl set image deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} \
            ${SERVICE_NAME}=${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${env.TAG_NAME} \
            -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE}-stg
          kubectl rollout status deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} \
            -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE}-stg --timeout=180s
        """
      }
    }

    stage('Regression Tests — STG') {
      when { tag 'v*' }
      steps {
        dir("apps/${SERVICE_NAME}") {
          sh 'mvn verify -Pintegration-tests -Dtest.env=stg -q'
        }
      }
      post {
        always {
          junit "apps/${SERVICE_NAME}/target/failsafe-reports/**/*.xml"
        }
      }
    }

    // ── GATE MANUAL — PROD ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
    stage('🔒 Go/No-Go — PROD') {
      when { tag 'v*' }
      steps {
        script {
          // El release-manager recibe tarea en Jira/Teams via Workflow Manager
          // y aprueba directamente en este input de Jenkins
          def approval = input(
            message: "Deploy ${SERVICE_NAME}:${env.TAG_NAME} to PRODUCTION?",
            submitter: 'release-manager',
            parameters: [
              choice(
                name: 'ACTION',
                choices: ['Go', 'No-Go'],
                description: 'Decisión de release'
              ),
              text(
                name: 'NOTES',
                defaultValue: '',
                description: 'Notas del release-manager (obligatorio en No-Go)'
              )
            ]
          )
          if (approval['ACTION'] == 'No-Go') {
            error("Release rechazado por release-manager: ${approval['NOTES']}")
          }
          echo "Release aprobado: ${env.TAG_NAME}"
        }
      }
    }

    stage('Deploy — PROD') {
      when { tag 'v*' }
      steps {
        sh """
          kubectl set image deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} \
            ${SERVICE_NAME}=${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${env.TAG_NAME} \
            -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE}
          kubectl rollout status deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} \
            -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE} --timeout=300s
        """
      }
    }

    stage('Post-Deploy Health Check — PROD') {
      when { tag 'v*' }
      steps {
        sh """
          for i in 1 2 3 4 5 6; do
            STATUS=\$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' \
              https://api.bankportal.meridian.com/actuator/health/readiness)
            if [ "\$STATUS" = "200" ]; then
              echo "Health check PASS — PROD operativo"
              exit 0
            fi
            echo "Attempt \$i — HTTP \$STATUS — waiting 15s..."
            sleep 15
          done
          echo "PROD health check FAILED — iniciando rollback automático"
          kubectl rollout undo deployment/${SERVICE_NAME} -n ${K8S_NAMESPACE}
          exit 1
        """
      }
    }

  } // end stages

  post {
    success {
      script {
        if (env.TAG_NAME) {
          echo "Release ${env.TAG_NAME} desplegado en PROD exitosamente"
          // Notificar al SM para cierre del gate en Workflow Manager
          sh """
            curl -s -X POST "${env.TEAMS_WEBHOOK}" \
              -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
              -d '{"text":"✅ PROD deploy exitoso: ${SERVICE_NAME} ${env.TAG_NAME} — BankPortal"}'
          """
        }
      }
    }
    failure {
      sh """
        curl -s -X POST "${env.TEAMS_WEBHOOK}" \
          -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
          -d '{"text":"🔴 Pipeline FAILED: ${SERVICE_NAME} build #${env.BUILD_NUMBER} — ${env.BUILD_URL}"}'
      """
    }
    always {
      // Limpiar imágenes locales para no saturar el agente
      sh "docker rmi ${REGISTRY}/${SERVICE_NAME}:${IMAGE_TAG} || true"
    }
  }
}
